div.p: Problem: While testing with a stable release (main) the RC was not moving the drone in negative direction.
Solution: apply a hotfix to the dev branch and release the update. Obvious bugs like this should have not passed the 'dev' stage in the first place. releases on main must be minimized.
Problem: developer 1 needs recent updates from developer 2

Solution: developer 1 and 2 must first merge to `
dev-sitl` branch following all relevant procedures
Case III:
Problem: developer 1 needs to add two small incoherent features

Solution: Take a branch from "dev-sitl" for "feature 1". Once done, merge "dev-sitl" into "feature 1" branch and create a PR. Take a branch from "feature 1" for "feature 2" (no need to wait until PR is approved). etc.
Problem: developer 1 needs to add two coherent features (same Epic)

Solution: Take a branch from "dev-sitl" for "epic/xyz". Branch "feature1",
"feature2", etc. from
"epic/xyz"
. Once done create a PR for
"epic/xyz" into
"dev-sitl"
.
